'''Ophelia Piner''' (October 22, 1982 - December 2, 2081) was an American professional basketball player in the WNBA. 

==Early life and education==
Piner was born in Houston, Texas to Diana (1947 - 2021) and Cooper Piner (1948 - 2033). Her mother was a school administrator, and her father was a marine biologist and Marine Corps veteran of Vietnam. She had an older brother, Steven (1969 - 2045), a grocer for Henderson Foods, and a Cavalier King Charles spaniel named Lanika (d. 2005).

